Date:8/23/2011 11:30:54 AM
From:Spekulatius
re CMI, PCAR - don't you think that the trend would go from modular design
(where you can choose your own engine for the truck chasis) to an integrated
design? the modular design is unique to the USA, as far as I know. For better
performance (gear, chasis, load) and integrated design would be better, imo,
which would leave engine only suppliers in the cold (or they get bought out).

I laughed at the story from decades ago, when Mercedes/Daimler bought
Freightliner and did not understand why anybody would choose a truck engine
from a different manufacturer. I think they got their ass kicked until they
realised that things work differently in the US.

Still, I think performance requires tight integration and I believe that this
will do away with the "Choose your own engine" a la carte menu when purchasing
trucks eventually.
