It does not matter for how much BAC can borrow short term debt. What BAC needs
is the confidence of their customers that they are going to be around,
otherwise the stock price deflation can quickly become a real issue in their
business dealings. The main asset of any financial company confidence - if
their customers loose confidence in BAC, they are dead in 24h.

Confidence is what WEB provides to BAC, in exchange for a yield premium on the
5B$ in equity (preferred count as equity for regulatory purposes). From the
strictly financial perspective, this deal is of course dilutive for
shareholders, but this is not strictly a financial perspective. The advantage
of WEB is he is a loan shark that is perceived as a "good guy" and well
meaning.. All the more reason to buy Brk.b stock, imo. I believe this is
actually a win-win situation even for BAC shareholders too.
